Turkish Government May Pay Widows Pensions, Hurriyet Reports

-- B y   S t e v e   B r y a n t
-- 
2011-03-17T06:24:28Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-17/turkish-government-may-pay-widows-pensions-hurriyet-reports.html
  Turkey  may pay a monthly allowance
of up to 250 lira ($156) to widows who have no state pension,
Hurriyet newspaper reported, citing State Minister Hayati
Yazici.  Yazici made the announcement in Ankara after the main
opposition party said it would enact a system of family support
payments if it’s elected in June 12 nationwide parliamentary
voting, the newspaper said.  Tazici said the cash payments could be made to about
150,000 women who’ve lost their husbands and have no pension of
their own, Hurriyet said.  Click here for web link  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
